        <h2>Tips for Accurate Tracking</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Be consistent:</strong> Track every day, not just around your period</li>
          <li><strong>Track multiple signs:</strong> Combining methods increases accuracy</li>
          <li><strong>Give it time:</strong> You need 3-6 cycles to establish your patterns</li>
          <li><strong>Note disruptions:</strong> Travel, illness, stress can affect your cycle</li>
          <li><strong>Keep it simple:</strong> Start with just dates, add other signs as you get comfortable</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Knowledge Is Power</h2>
        <p>Your menstrual cycle isn't just about periods and pregnancy — it's a vital sign that reflects your overall health. By understanding your unique pattern, you become a better advocate for your own health.</p>

        <p>Start simple. Track consistently. And remember — everyone's cycle is different. What matters is understanding yours.</p>
